<br>
1.  Sick of the Stealth Nerfs.  Verant, if you want to nerf us, say &quot;We are nerfing this song because it is overpowered.&quot;  Tell us the truth.  DON'T say &quot;We apologize for the accidental problems with Chains.  The song will be returned to its proper state shortly.&quot;  If you think Lullaby is a level 30 and under song, FUCKING TELL US.  DON'T BEAT AROUND THE GOD DAMNED BUSH.  It has been MONTHS AND MONTHS since GZ's test.  Never once were we told &quot;The song is not intended to be efficient post 30.&quot;  Never mind that this explanation doesn't even make SENSE:  ALL BARD SONGS DO EITHER ONE OF 2 THINGS- 1.  Grow in power as the bard levels.  2.  Are upgraded when the bard obtains a reasonable level.  Lullaby does none of these things.  It is OBVIOUS that despite what Verant claims, NO-ONE in-house plays a bard.  No-one in house even understands basic bard issues.  Our songs have been made useless one at a time:  Our resist buffs, because of the bug where if you exceed 255 resist, 255 is SUBTRACTED from your resist.  Our Mesmerize/Lullaby songs, by the adding of a secondary resist.  Our DoT's were hit hard by the druid nurf, as we have no way of parking mobs- if we wish to solo with DoT's, we are stuck with snaring or running quickly from them.  Of course, now our Haste Songs get hit as well- no longer can we come NEAR the haste buff of another class.<br>
<br>
2.  The worthlessness of our class.  Fact is, bards are good for one thing- pumping mana.  I've looked through EVERY SINGLE SONG I HAVE- which is 51, all told.  I can only think of 1 that has a significant use in a group- pumping mana.  Our attack buffs are good for nothing but stats.  Pity stats are basically useless anyway.  Resists?  Bugged.  Psalm?  9 damage?  Useless against 12k+ HP mobs.  Charm?  Takes me over a full bubble of mana to charm a 2-mob pull in Sebilis.  In many locations, root-planting is a far superior alternative.  Our melee has degenerated in comparison to other classes post 50.  Fact is, we're mana batteries, nothing more.<br>
<br>
3.  THE FACT THAT KUNARK IS A PIECE OF CRAP.  This is easily the most ill-created expansion Verant could have thought to create.  They gave us dungeons more designed around &quot;doing&quot; them than about getting experience in them.  The one &quot;exp dungeon&quot; (Karnors) is basically unplayable, because piss-poor pathing creates horrific trains.  Mobs gating is another shitty idea, in the Verant style of &quot;Make them cheesy instead of Hard!&quot;  Examples:  Dispell, Fear, CH, Gating, Trakanons Touch, Mobs in VP &quot;reality warping.&quot;  The other 2 50+ dungeons (Sebilis and Charasis) require a well-built group, with an enchanter, a cleric, and an evaccer.  For almost all locations in these dungeons, a tank is needed as well, possibly 2.  This leaves remaining classes (bards, necros, mages) scrambling for one spot.  Not to mention that these zones require significant travel to get to and significant work to even enter.<br>
<br>
Going out to dinner with friends, I'll finish post when I return. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ukaluianismyname.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaluian is my name</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(9/19/00 7:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *sighs*... has it happened?</span><hr size=1> I'm back from dinner.  Yes, it was good.<br>
<br>
Anyway, continuing with point 3.<br>
<br>
... Significant Work to even enter.  Not to mention breaking a camp in one of these zones requires a significant time investment.  For example, a typical crypt break-in- <br>
15 minutes:  Wait for group to form.<br>
3 minutes:  Buff everyone up.<br>
5 minutes:  Kill everything up to rock 3-spawn.<br>
3 minutes:  Med at rock.<br>
7 minutes: Clear from Bridge to Temple.<br>
3 minutes:  Med up.<br>
5 minutes:  Clear first 2 undead rooms.<br>
3 minutes:  Med up at stairs prior to Crypt.<br>
5 minutes:  Clear room behind us and roamers.<br>
3 minutes:  Med up.<br>
4 minutes:  Kill both Imperial Crypt Guardians.<br>
2 minutes:  Med up.<br>
TOTAL:  53 minutes.  This is if we are lucky and there are no unexpected delays and doesn't logically happen.  Before Kunark, people complained that &quot;Unless you have an hour or more, there's nothing to do in this game.&quot;  Look above!  Now, an hour will simply GET YOU TO A SPOT- let alone getting a solitary PIXEL of experience!  Hell, back in the good old days, it would be something like:<br>
Log in.<br>
1 minute:  /shout XX Bard looking for group.<br>
1 minute:  Soandso tells you &quot;Hey, the Magi could use a bard.&quot;<br>
1 minute:  Get invis undead (not really necessary).<br>
1 minute:  Run to Magi.<br>
TOTAL:  4 minutes until I'm off and getting experience!  If I camped Freeport, add 7 minutes for the run.  If I have trouble finding a group, add 5 minutes.  During these 5 minutes, I can easily solo mobs at live zone line area, getting more exp than in the full hour in Seb!<br>
<br>
The game has changed, and not for the better.  I have commitments during the day, and can't afford to stay up very late.  I have about 4 hours to play on a typical weekday.  This is not enough time to form a full balanced group- cleric preferably, but sham or druid can work- enc, evac, tank or 2, and me.  Since there's just about no way to get down to a camp in Seb/Charasis, unless you're a monk or rogue, the old zone in and shout doesn't work anymore.  Frankly, Kunark is a joke.  The only times I can hope to even group with my friends are weekends.  Oh yeah, and...<br>
<br>
CLUE TO VERANT:  OUTDOOR ZONES ARE BORING AS ALL HELL!<br>
<br>
I'm sorry, but I'm a dungeon crawler.  The method of &quot;pull/fear/snare/fear/snare/fear/snare&quot; doesn't work for me.  I can solo just as well as any other class, but I would rather not.  BAH!<br>
<br>
With this in mind, I have created a wizard, who I may or may not play semi-seriously.  We shall see. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ulyrniajongleur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lyrnia Jongleur</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(9/19/00 10:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *sighs*... has it happened?</span><hr size=1> /em nods at Kaluian<br>
