In answer to the subject line question, I don`t know.<br>
<br>
Here is a typical EQ night:<br>
Log in. Tell the guild hello. Ask if anyone needs a bard in Seb, Karnor, DL, whatever. Greeted with the usual sound of crickets chirping, I fall into conversation with my friends. I get a sow, and kite a few mobs. However, kiting for 4 hours and watching 2 pixels move on my experience bar is disheartening, and more importantly, not_fun. After a few mobs, I usually log off. Maybe log on Kaluienne and check the auctions in Freeport. Maybe log onto another server and visit my friends. Log off and check a messagge board or 2. Log back on and ask for a group again. Log and go to bed, go to eat, go to a movie, whatever.<br>
<br>
I`ve also become disheartened with my class in general. No matter what anyone says, I`ve become convinced that the bard is now nothing more than a mana battery. Perhaps in solo, duo, or small group outdoor situations, a bard is a great addition. Actually, there is no perhaps- a bard IS a great addition to a group. However, that is not where I want to play the game. My game is played in dungeons, in the midst of danger, and on raids. What role can a bard play there? Before the expansion, I could do a great deal. The old saying goes &quot;jack of all trades, master of none.&quot; Before the expansion, I was an OK tank- some Guk camps I could tank. I was an OK healer- if a group could survive the fight, I could heal them up quickly. I was an OK enchanter- I could do crowd control on a pull of 3 mobs, sometimes more. My haste buffs made the warriors swords speed up, my debuffs made the monsters fists slow down. All and all, I was not indispensable, but I was useful and helpful in a group.<br>
<br>
What about post-expansion? I can`t tank shit. Send me into Sebilis or Karnor and try to ask me to tank ONE mob. Hell, send me into DL and ask me to tank one mob! I`m a WORTHLESS healer- name one group that survives a fight without needing a heal. Even if they do, my heals take so long to work it`d be multiple minutes between fights. I`m a shitty enchanter- I can do a half-decent job in Karnor, but in Seb? Chardok? Hahaha. IF you pull 2, then I can do crowd control. For 5 pulls. The new charm is limited by mana use, and controlling one creature for a fast Seb fight takes a bubble of mana- and clarity, manasong, med does not effect me. My haste buffs no longer makes swords swing faster- Haste Buff + Haste item bring you to the haste cap. The addition of the stats is worthless. My haste debuffs aggro mobs through walls, are heavily resisted, and are a massive taunt. Even if they weren`t, a host of other classes can do a better job. My melee is a joke.<br>
<br>
All I have left is my mana. Excuse the phrase, but fuck that. I always told myself I would not be a mana bard. There is so much more to playing a bard. Bards can do so much more for a group... well, the time has come. We can`t. My use in a dungeon is often limited to &quot;sit your ass down and play manasong.&quot; <br>
<br>
Soo... thanks for the pie Andy, but I'll just eat it- I hope you're a good cook ;-)<br>
